jel and syphilis) were present in late medieval Europe. In doing so, the author hopes to spark a conversation not only about the existence of the disease in various places and times, but also its wider impact on premodern society and culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 0aBejelxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aPaleopathology. 0aSyphiliszEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 0aTreponematoseszEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 7aMEDICAL / History.2bisacsh  aPaleopathology.  aancient and medieval Eurasia.  asyphilis.  atreponematosis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802700893?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802700893423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802700893/original  a978-3-11-076709-4  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aEBA_CL_MDPM  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MDPM  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK